                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1123 Coltman, Charles/87: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-05-26T15:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 26, 1923—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 26—7:02 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>184. My 171, May 19, 11 a.m.<note n="54" xml:id="d592fn54">Not printed.</note>
                    Note from Foreign Office dated yesterday states chief of staff on petition
                    Ministry War and General <pb facs="0854" n="738" xml:id="pg_738"/> Staff was
                    dismissed by Presidential mandate, and chief adjutant and Adjutant Wang
                    dismissed by Ministry of War; and Chinese Government accepts our demand for
                    $25,000 compensation.<note n="55" xml:id="d592fn55">On Sept. 20, the Chinese
                        Acting Minister for Foreign Affairs transmitted a draft for $25,000 to the
                        Minister in China in payment of this claim.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
